# .cursorrules

# CHYTAYKO MASTER CONTRACT
# Mobile application
# Stack: Expo + React Native + Firebase
# Product: Chytayko
# Source of truth:
# - docs/TECHNICAL_PASSPORT.md
# - docs/DESIGN_CODE.md

---

## ROLE

You are working on Chytayko.

Chytayko is:

- mobile application
- portfolio project
- reading-first experience
- parents + children (4+)
- Expo application
- React Native application
- Firebase backend

You are NOT building:

- SaaS
- marketplace
- social network
- admin system
- AI platform
- payment product

Primary goal:

Build stable MVP only.

Never expand scope.

---

## SOURCE OF TRUTH

Always read first:

1. docs/TECHNICAL_PASSPORT.md
2. docs/DESIGN_CODE.md

Priority:

TECHNICAL_PASSPORT:

controls

- product
- architecture
- Firebase
- storage
- flows
- naming
- MVP limits

DESIGN_CODE:

controls

- UI
- UX
- themes
- colors
- reader
- motion
- illustrations
- accessibility

Never violate these documents.

If conflict exists:

TECHNICAL_PASSPORT wins for architecture.

DESIGN_CODE wins for UI.

---

## STACK FREEZE

Frozen stack:

Expo

React Native

Firebase Auth

Firestore

Firebase Storage

Allowed:

TypeScript

Expo Router

React Navigation

NativeWind

React Query

Forbidden:

Backend server

Node API

Express

Nest

Microservices

PostgreSQL

MongoDB

Redis

Docker

Payments

Subscriptions

AI integrations

Push notifications

Offline mode

Admin panel

Cloud Functions

Scope expansion

Do not introduce new technologies without request.

---

## ARCHITECTURE RULES

Use feature architecture only.

Preferred structure:

src/

app/

components/

features/

auth/

stories/

reader/

favorites/

profile/

services/

firebase/

theme/

tokens/

hooks/

types/

utils/

assets/

Rules:

No business logic in screens.

Firebase access only inside services.

No direct Firestore calls inside UI.

Use reusable components.

Avoid coupling.

Prefer composition.

No screen hacks.

No duplicate logic.

---

## FIREBASE RULES

Use only:

Auth

Firestore

Storage

Rules:

No open collections.

No public writes.

Favorites:

owner only

Progress:

owner only

Users:

owner only

Stories:

read only

Pages:

read only

Storage:

WEBP only

Sequential naming:

page-001.webp

page-002.webp

page-003.webp

Never:

allow read, write: if true;

Never expose secrets.

Never hardcode IDs.

Never bypass ownership.

---

## UI RULES

Follow:

Nordic Quiet Minimal

Themes:

Nordic Paper

Night Story

Reader-first UX.

Always support:

Light mode

Dark mode

Use tokens only.

No hardcoded colors.

No inline spacing.

No random typography.

No visual experiments.

Forbidden:

Disney style

Game UI

Bank UI

Government style

Neon

Heavy gradients

Glassmorphism overload

Visual chaos

Tiny buttons

Dense layouts

Reader clutter

---

## READER RULES

Reader is highest priority screen.

Reader must:

Feel calm

Support bedtime reading

Use large text

Use soft contrast

Hide bottom navigation

Support dark mode

Allow page navigation

Allow progress

Allow favorite

Forbidden:

Ads

Gamification

Toolbar overload

Bright controls

Complex menus

Multiple actions

Visual noise

Reader experience wins over all other screens.

---

## DESIGN IMPLEMENTATION RULES

Use:

Color tokens

Spacing tokens

Radius tokens

Typography tokens

Motion tokens

Illustration contract

Accessibility rules

Never create new theme systems.

Never add new palettes.

Never change typography scale.

Never reduce touch targets.

Keep:

Large spacing

Air

Calm interaction

Minimal motion

---

## TEXT RULES

Language:

Ukrainian only for MVP.

Future:

Norwegian

English

Rules:

No inline strings.

Centralize text.

Avoid duplication.

Avoid mixed languages.

---

## PERFORMANCE RULES

Images:

WEBP only

100–200 KB preferred

Use lazy loading.

Never load all stories.

Use pagination.

Avoid:

PNG

Large assets

Repeated downloads

Heavy backgrounds

Full library fetch

---

## DEVELOPMENT RULES

Build order:

1. Project setup

2. Theme system

3. Navigation

4. Firebase

5. Authentication

6. Stories

7. Story details

8. Reader

9. Favorites

10. Progress

11. Profile

12. Polish

No skipping.

No parallel scope expansion.

One feature at a time.

Finish before moving.

---

## CHANGE RULES

Before changing anything:

Read:

TECHNICAL_PASSPORT

↓

Read:

DESIGN_CODE

↓

Check:

Nordic Quiet Minimal

↓

Implement

If feature is outside MVP:

STOP

Request confirmation.

---

## COMMAND EXECUTION RULES

Cursor MUST NOT run:

- git commands
- npm install
- npm audit fix
- npm audit fix --force
- npm start
- npx expo start
- expo-doctor
- tsc
- tsc --noEmit
- lint
- tests
- build commands
- Metro
- emulator commands
- simulator commands

Cursor may only edit files.

After each change, Cursor must tell the user what command the user should run manually.

Cursor must never claim that something “passes” unless the user has run the command and provided the result.

---

## OUTPUT RULES

Output only:

Files changed

Changes

Manual checks for user

No explanations.

No feature ideas.

No expansion proposals.

No extra architecture.

No unsolicited refactoring.

---

## FREEZE

Frozen:

Expo

React Native

Firebase

Reader-first UX

Nordic Quiet Minimal

Parents + children 4+

UA MVP

No backend

No AI

No payments

No subscriptions

No admin panel

Expansion allowed only after MVP completion.

